@page "/modules/datamodeling"
@using System.Text.Json
@using Microsoft.JSInterop
@inject DataModelingApiClient Api
@inject BenchmarkService Benchmark
@inject Microsoft.JSInterop.IJSRuntime JS
@implements IDisposable

<PageTitle>Data Modeling - Learn Cosmos DB</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Data Modeling</h1>
    <span class="page-subtitle">A guided walkthrough of document modeling in Azure Cosmos DB</span>
</div>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 1 — About
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <p>
        While there are multiple considerations in Cosmos DB for optimizing performance, understanding
        <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/modeling-data" target="_blank">data modeling</a>
        and implementing it effectively can be critical in getting the best experience. This walkthrough reviews different
        methods of modeling in Cosmos DB and demonstrates the benefits of thinking in a non-relational way. 
    </p>

    <h3>Scenario</h3>
    <p>
        Consider a media streaming site that wants a fast browsing experience for users located around the world.
        Movie information is created by studios and is generally consistent, but the flexibility of being schema-less is also
        a need. Cosmos DB, as a NoSQL database, allows us to adjust the schema as needed without redefining the entire
        database schema like you might need in a relational database.
    </p>
    <p>
        The browsing pattern we are optimizing for: a user searches a movie title, the results show a director,
        they click the director to see other movies, then select a movie from those results. We will walk through four
        different document models each using the same data and same <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/partitioning-overview#choose-partitionkey" target="_blank">partition key</a> to see how
        the RU cost changes based on how the data is structured.
    </p>
    <p>
        When considering costs, we expect any given time there are ~1,000 concurrent users performing searches.
    </p>

</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 2 — Single Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2 id="section-Single">Starting Model — "Single"</h2>
    <p>
        To try and balance our partitions, we went with a partitioning
        method of using the movie title as our partition key. Each document in our container is a single movie with the following structure.
    </p>
    <div class="schema-example">
        <div class="schema-example-label">Example Single Movie Document</div>
        <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "1234567890",
    "type": "movie",
    "title": "single doc movie",
    "originalTitle": "Single Doc Movie",
    "tagline": "A great tagline",
    "description": "A movie about data modeling.",
    "mpaaRating": "PG-13",
    "releaseDate": "2001-06-15",
    "year": 2001,
    "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg",
    "genres": [
        {
            "name": "Action",
            "id": "g001"
        }
    ],
    "directors": [
        {
            "name": "best director",
            "originalName": "Best Director",
            "id": "0987654321"
        }
    ],
    "actors": [
        {
            "name": "best actor",
            "originalName": "Best Actor",
            "id": "1029384576"
        }
    ],
    "reviews": [
        {
            "id": "r001",
            "criticReview": "A thrilling ride.",
            "criticScore": 8.5
        }
    ]
}</pre>
    </div>
    <p>
        Since a user does not know the unique ID of a movie, searching on a movie title allows a partition-based query
        with lower RU cost. However, searching for a director or actor is embedded information and requires a a more complex and cross-partition
        query. This requires the user to specify the search type (movie vs. person).
    </p>
    <p>
        Walk through the three steps below to see the RU cost at each stage simulating the search pattern of movie, director and selecting a movie.
    </p>

    @{ var single = sections["Single"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(single, "Single")

    @{ var singleActive = GetActiveResponse(single); }
    @if (singleActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (singleActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> This query searches on the movie title, which is the partition key. This means the
                query is scoped to a single partition.
            </div>
        }
        @if (singleActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> The Single model required a separate query based upon explicitly making it a person search. 
                This required a cross partition query that used an <code>ARRAY_CONTAINS</code> method and just added complexity to both code and UI.
            </div>
        }
        @if (singleActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Since we know the exact document ID and partition key from the previous results,
                this is a point read which is typically the cheapest query method for small documents like the ones we utilize.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(singleActive.Response, singleActive.Label, singleActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)", "results-Single")
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 3 — Embedded Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2 id="section-Embedded">Embedded Model</h2>
    <p>
        Starting to rethink this mode, we improved searching by creating a collocated document for each Actor and Director for a given movie. The data is
        embedded just like the movie document with some minor changes to properties, primarily making the document title the person rather than the movie.
        This simplified application logic and improved user experience, removing the need to specify a search type. The movie documents remain unchanged.
    </p>
    <div class="schema-example">
        <div class="schema-example-label">Example Embedded Person Document</div>
        <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "mov12345act6789",
    "type": "person",
    "title": "best actor",
    "originalTitle": "Best Actor",
    "movieId": "1234567890",
    "movieTitle": "Single Doc Movie",
    "tagline": "A great tagline",
    "description": "A movie about data modeling.",
    "mpaaRating": "PG-13",
    "releaseDate": "2001-06-15",
    "year": 2001,
    "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg",
    "genres": [
        {
            "name": "Action",
            "id": "g001"
        }
    ],
    "directors": [
        {
            "name": "best director",
            "originalName": "Best Director",
            "id": "0987654321"
        }
    ],
    "actors": [
        {
            "name": "best actor",
            "originalName": "Best Actor",
            "id": "1029384576"
        }
    ],
    "reviews": [
        {
            "id": "r001",
            "criticReview": "A thrilling ride.",
            "criticScore": 8.5
        }
    ]
}</pre>
    </div>
    <p>
        Since we query on a partition value (the person's name), the director search cost is reduced significantly.
        However, these person documents duplicate the full movie data and increasing storage needed substantially.
        While storage is a miminmal part of overall cost it was a tradeoff to greatly reduce the RU's needed for our query patterns.
    </p>

    @{ var embedded = sections["Embedded"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(embedded, "Embedded")

    @{ var embeddedActive = GetActiveResponse(embedded); }
    @if (embeddedActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (embeddedActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> The movie search is identical to the Single model but this Embedded model improved person searches.
            </div>
        }
        @if (embeddedActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> No search type is needed as the query is a simple partition-key lookup
                on the director's name and removing the cross partition query reduced the cost heavily.
            </div>
        }
        @if (embeddedActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Point read on the movie document using ID and partition key, same RU cost
                as the Single model.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(embeddedActive.Response, embeddedActive.Label, embeddedActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)", "results-Embedded")
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 4 — Reference Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2 id="section-Reference">Reference Model</h2>
    <p>
        Rethinking this more carefully, we used the same collocation method but changed the person documents to only contain
        basic reference data for the movie. We realized with query and browsing patterns the rich details of each movie for a person focused search was not necessary.
    </p>
    <div class="schema-example">
        <div class="schema-example-label">Example Reference Person Document</div>
        <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "mov12345act6789",
    "type": "person",
    "title": "best actor",
    "originalTitle": "Best Actor",
    "movieId": "1234567890",
    "movieTitle": "Single Doc Movie",
    "mpaaRating": "PG-13",
    "releaseDate": "2001-06-15",
    "year": 2001,
    "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg"
}</pre>
    </div>
    <p>
        We lose embedded details like descriptions, taglines and reviews, but those were not used during browsing.
        This reduced the amount of data in our person collocated documents greatly reduced the document size while also futher reducing RU costs.
    </p>

    @{ var reference = sections["Reference"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(reference, "Reference")

    @{ var referenceActive = GetActiveResponse(reference); }
    @if (referenceActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (referenceActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Like all other models, Movie search is the same partition-key query as the movie documents are unchanged
                across all models.
            </div>
        }
        @if (referenceActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> The Reference model uses slimmer person documents with only basic movie data.
                The smaller document size results in a slightly lower RU cost compared to the Embedded model while also reducing storage requirements.
            </div>
        }
        @if (referenceActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Point read retrieves the full movie document same cost as other models since
                the movie documents are identical across all four containers.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(referenceActive.Response, referenceActive.Label, referenceActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)", "results-Reference")
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 5 — Hybrid Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2 id="section-Hybrid">Hybrid Model</h2>
    <p>
        As a final design we combined the partition-based query approach from the Embedded model with the smaller document size from
        the Reference model. Each person has a single document containing
        a roles array with reference data for each movie. This can be obtained with a partition query or
        even a Point Read by allowing only a single document result.
    </p>
    <div class="schema-example">
        <div class="schema-example-label">Example Hybrid Person Document</div>
        <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "act123",
    "title": "best actor",
    "originalTitle": "Best Actor",
    "type": "person",
    "roles": [
        {
            "movieId": "13579",
            "movieTitle": "Movie 1",
            "mpaaRating": "PG",
            "releaseDate": "1901-03-10",
            "year": 1901,
            "posterUrl": "https://example.com/movie1.jpg",
            "roleName": "Lead Hero"
        },
        {
            "movieId": "24680",
            "movieTitle": "Movie 2",
            "mpaaRating": "R",
            "releaseDate": "1902-07-22",
            "year": 1902,
            "posterUrl": "https://example.com/movie2.jpg",
            "roleName": "Villain"
        }
    ]
}</pre>
    </div>
    <p>
        The director search cost drops to nearly match the movie search cost. Once a user starts browsing by
        clicking results, subsequent queries can be Point Reads.
    </p>

    @{ var hybrid = sections["Hybrid"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(hybrid, "Hybrid")

    @{ var hybridActive = GetActiveResponse(hybrid); }
    @if (hybridActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (hybridActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Movie search remains the same partition-key query across all models.
            </div>
        }
        @if (hybridActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> The director search is now nearly as cheap as a movie search. A single person
                document contains all movie references in a <code>roles</code> array. Retrieving one result from one partition.
            </div>
        }
        @if (hybridActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Point read on the selected movie. With the Hybrid model, once a user starts
                browsing by clicking results, every subsequent query can be a Point Read for both movies and persons.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(hybridActive.Response, hybridActive.Label, hybridActive.Label == "Select Movie (Point Read)", "results-Hybrid")
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 6 — Summary
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section id="section-Summary" class="guide-section guide-section-last">
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
        By rethinking our data model and taking advantage of the schema-less design of Cosmos DB, we were able to take the
        same data and even the same partition key and achieve a vastly improved performance experience by modeling the data
        to fit the use case.
    </p>

    @{
        bool allComplete = sections.Values.All(s => s.Step == SectionStep.DetailDone);
    }
    @if (allComplete)
    {
        var singleTotal = Benchmark.GetModelTotal("Single");
        var embeddedTotal = Benchmark.GetModelTotal("Embedded");
        var referenceTotal = Benchmark.GetModelTotal("Reference");
        var hybridTotal = Benchmark.GetModelTotal("Hybrid");
        var worstTotal = singleTotal;
        var bestTotal = new[] { singleTotal, embeddedTotal, referenceTotal, hybridTotal }.Min();
        var bestModel = hybridTotal == bestTotal ? "Hybrid" : referenceTotal == bestTotal ? "Reference" : embeddedTotal == bestTotal ? "Embedded" : "Single";
        var savings = worstTotal > 0 ? ((worstTotal - bestTotal) / worstTotal * 100) : 0;
        var multiplier = bestTotal > 0 ? (worstTotal / bestTotal) : 0;

        <div class="summary-cost-analysis">
            <p>
                Based on searching for movie <strong>"@hints?.MovieTitle"</strong> and director <strong>"@hints?.TopDirectorName"</strong>,
                here is how each model compares:
            </p>
            <table class="cost-table summary-cost-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Model</th>
                        @foreach (var action in Benchmark.ActionNames)
                        {
                            <th>@action</th>
                        }
                        <th>Total RU (1 Request)</th>
                        <th>RU × 1,000 Requests/sec</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    @foreach (var model in Benchmark.ModelNames)
                    {
                        var total = Benchmark.GetModelTotal(model);
                        var isBest = model == bestModel;
                        <tr class="@(isBest ? "summary-best-row" : "")">
                            <td>@model</td>
                            @foreach (var action in Benchmark.ActionNames)
                            {
                                var cost = Benchmark.GetCost(model, action);
                                <td>@cost.ToString("F2") RU</td>
                            }
                            <td><strong>@total.ToString("F2") RU</strong></td>
                            <td>@((total * 1000).ToString("N0")) RU/s</td>
                        </tr>
                    }
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <div class="summary-savings-callout">
                <strong>@bestModel</strong> saved <strong>@savings.ToString("F0")%</strong> in RU cost compared to the Single model
                A <strong>@multiplier.ToString("F1")×</strong> improvement.
                At 1,000 requests/sec that's <strong>@((worstTotal * 1000).ToString("N0")) RU/s</strong> vs
                <strong>@((bestTotal * 1000).ToString("N0")) RU/s</strong>, saving
                <strong>@(((worstTotal - bestTotal) * 1000).ToString("N0")) RU/s</strong>.
            </div>
            <div style="text-align: right;">
                <button class="start-over-btn" @onclick="StartOver">↺ Start Over</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    }

    <p>
        Given the scenario of 1,000 concurrent users performing these actions, the Hybrid model achieves a high
        performance improvement while also providing an improved application experience. The only key influencers would be the 
        number of movies per person which in the realm of reality is not likely to be large for a vast amount of the various actors and directors.
        As the overall count of documents would increase the RU of the Single and other models would increase at a rate much higher than the hybrid model
        providing better long term scalability as well.
    </p>
    <p>
        There is no one-size-fits-all solution, but you will find there are many ways to get great performance out of
        Cosmos DB with data modeling.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="/demos/datamodeling" class="guide-demo-link">Data Modeling demo</a>
        Explore all four models with other search values and interactive patterns.
    </p>
</section>

<div id="dm-page-end"></div>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Floating Cost Comparison Table
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
@if (HasAnyCosts())
{
    <div class="guide-cost-tracker">
        <div class="cost-minimized-icon"><img src="learncosmos.webp" alt="LearnCosmosDB" class="cost-mini-logo" /></div>
        <div class="cost-tracker-header">
            <span class="cost-tracker-title">Cost Comparison</span>
            <button class="benchmark-clear" title="Reset all costs" @onclick="ResetAll">↺</button>
        </div>
        @if (hints is not null)
        {
            <div class="cost-tracker-search-values">
                Movie: <strong>@hints.MovieTitle</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Director: <strong>@hints.TopDirectorName</strong>
            </div>
        }
        <table class="cost-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Model</th>
                    @foreach (var action in Benchmark.ActionNames)
                    {
                        <th>@action</th>
                    }
                    <th>Total</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                @foreach (var model in Benchmark.ModelNames)
                {
                    @if (Benchmark.GetModelTotal(model) > 0)
                    {
                        <tr>
                            <td><a class="cost-model-link" href="javascript:void(0)" @onclick='() => ScrollToSection(model)'>@model</a></td>
                            @foreach (var action in Benchmark.ActionNames)
                            {
                                var cost = Benchmark.GetCost(model, action);
                                <td class="@(cost > 0 ? "cost-active" : "")">@cost.ToString("F2") RU</td>
                            }
                            @{ var total = Benchmark.GetModelTotal(model); }
                            <td class="cost-total @(total > 0 ? "cost-active" : "")"><strong>@total.ToString("F2") RU</strong></td>
                        </tr>
                    }
                }
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
}

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Render Fragments
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
@{
    RenderFragment RenderStepButtons(SectionState sec, string model) => __builder2 =>
    {
        var isMovie = sec.Step == SectionStep.Ready;
        var isDirector = sec.Step == SectionStep.MovieDone;
        var isDetail = sec.Step == SectionStep.DirectorDone;
        var isDone = sec.Step == SectionStep.DetailDone;
        var isWorking = sec.IsLoading;

        <div class="guide-step-row" id="steps-@model">
            <button class="guide-step-btn @(sec.Step > SectionStep.Ready ? "guide-step-done" : "") @(isMovie ? "guide-step-active" : "")"
                    disabled="@(!isMovie || isWorking)"
                    @onclick="() => DoMovieSearch(model)">
                @StepLabel("1. Search Movie", isWorking && isMovie, sec.Step > SectionStep.Ready)
            </button>
            <span class="guide-step-arrow">→</span>
            <button class="guide-step-btn @(sec.Step > SectionStep.MovieDone ? "guide-step-done" : "") @(isDirector ? "guide-step-active" : "")"
                    disabled="@(!isDirector || isWorking)"
                    @onclick="() => DoDirectorSearch(model)">
                @StepLabel("2. Search Director", isWorking && isDirector, sec.Step > SectionStep.MovieDone)
            </button>
            <span class="guide-step-arrow">→</span>
            <button class="guide-step-btn @(sec.Step > SectionStep.DirectorDone ? "guide-step-done" : "") @(isDetail ? "guide-step-active" : "")"
                    disabled="@(!isDetail || isWorking)"
                    @onclick="() => DoDetailClick(model)">
                @StepLabel("3. Select Movie", isWorking && isDetail, sec.Step > SectionStep.DirectorDone)
            </button>

            @if (isDone || sec.Step > SectionStep.Ready)
            {
                <button class="guide-step-reset" title="Reset this section" @onclick="() => ResetSection(model)">↺</button>
            }
        </div>

        @if (sec.Error is not null)
        {
            <div class="error-message">@(sec.Error)</div>
        }
    };

    RenderFragment RenderResultsPanel(DataModelingResponse resp, string label, bool isDetail = false, string? anchorId = null) => __builder2 =>
    {
        <div class="guide-results-label" id="@anchorId">@label</div>
        <div class="results-panel">
            <div class="panel panel-left">
                <div class="diag-summary">
                    <h3>Query Diagnostics</h3>
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">RU Cost</span>
                        <span class="diag-value ru-highlight">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.RequestCharge RU</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">Query Type</span>
                        <span class="diag-value">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryType</span>
                    </div>
                    @if (resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryText is not null)
                    {
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Query</span>
                            <span class="diag-value" style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.78rem;">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryText</span>
                        </div>
                    }
                    @if (resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryType == "Point Read")
                    {
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Document ID</span>
                            <span class="diag-value diag-truncate">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.DocId</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Partition Key</span>
                            <span class="diag-value diag-truncate">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.FormattedSearchValue</span>
                        </div>
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Search Value</span>
                            <span class="diag-value">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.SubmittedSearchValue</span>
                        </div>
                    }
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">Data Model</span>
                        <span class="diag-value">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.DataModel</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">Documents</span>
                        <span class="diag-value">@resp.MediaResults.Count</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                @if (resp.MediaResults.Count > 0)
                {
                    <h3 style="margin-top: 1rem;">Raw JSON</h3>
                    <pre class="doc-json">@FormatJson(resp.MediaResults[0])</pre>
                }
            </div>

            <div class="panel-right">
                @if (isDetail && resp.MediaResults.Count > 0)
                {
                    @* ── Movie Detail View ── *@
                    var m = resp.MediaResults[0];
                    var detailTitle = GetProp(m, "originalTitle") ?? GetProp(m, "title") ?? "";
                    var detailPoster = GetProp(m, "posterUrl");
                    var detailYear = GetProp(m, "year") ?? "";
                    var detailRating = GetProp(m, "mpaaRating") ?? "";
                    var detailDesc = GetProp(m, "description") ?? GetProp(m, "tagline") ?? "";
                    var detailTagline = GetProp(m, "tagline") ?? "";
                    var detailGenres = GetArray(m, "genres");
                    var detailActors = GetPeople(m, "actors");
                    var detailDirectors = GetPeople(m, "directors");
                    var detailReviews = GetReviews(m);

                    <div class="panel movie-detail">
                        <div class="detail-header">
                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(detailPoster))
                            {
                                <img class="detail-poster" src="@detailPoster" alt="@detailTitle" />
                            }
                            else
                            {
                                <div class="detail-poster-placeholder">🎬</div>
                            }
                            <div class="detail-info">
                                <h2 class="detail-title">@detailTitle</h2>
                                <div class="detail-meta">
                                    <div class="detail-meta-left">
                                        @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(detailYear)) { <span class="detail-badge">@detailYear</span> }
                                        @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(detailRating)) { <span class="detail-badge rating">@detailRating</span> }
                                        @foreach (var g in detailGenres)
                                        {
                                            <span class="detail-badge genre">@g</span>
                                        }
                                    </div>
                                    @if (detailReviews.Count > 0)
                                    {
                                        var scores = detailReviews
                                            .Where(r => double.TryParse(r.Score, out _))
                                            .Select(r => double.Parse(r.Score))
                                            .ToList();
                                        @if (scores.Count > 0)
                                        {
                                            var avgScore = scores.Average();
                                            var rating10 = avgScore > 10 ? avgScore / 10.0 : avgScore;
                                            <span class="detail-badge cosmos-rating" title="Average critic score">
                                                <svg class="planet-icon" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                                                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/>
                                                    <ellipse cx="12" cy="12" rx="11" ry="4" transform="rotate(-20 12 12)"/>
                                                </svg>
                                                @rating10.ToString("F1") / 10
                                            </span>
                                        }
                                    }
                                </div>
                                @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(detailTagline))
                                {
                                    <p class="detail-tagline">"@detailTagline"</p>
                                }
                                <div class="detail-description">
                                    <p>@detailDesc</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        @if (detailDirectors.Count > 0)
                        {
                            <div class="detail-section">
                                <h3>Directors</h3>
                                <div class="detail-people">
                                    @foreach (var (name, originalName, imageUrl) in detailDirectors)
                                    {
                                        <span class="person-card-link">
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(imageUrl))
                                            {
                                                <img class="person-avatar" src="@imageUrl" alt="@originalName"
                                                     onerror="this.style.display='none';this.nextElementSibling.style.display='flex';" />
                                                <span class="person-avatar-placeholder" style="display:none;">
                                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="silhouette-icon"><circle cx="32" cy="24" r="12"/><ellipse cx="32" cy="56" rx="20" ry="14"/></svg>
                                                </span>
                                            }
                                            else
                                            {
                                                <span class="person-avatar-placeholder">
                                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="silhouette-icon"><circle cx="32" cy="24" r="12"/><ellipse cx="32" cy="56" rx="20" ry="14"/></svg>
                                                </span>
                                            }
                                            <span class="person-name">@originalName</span>
                                        </span>
                                    }
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        }

                        @if (detailActors.Count > 0)
                        {
                            <div class="detail-section">
                                <h3>Cast</h3>
                                <div class="detail-people">
                                    @foreach (var (name, originalName, imageUrl) in detailActors)
                                    {
                                        <span class="person-card-link">
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(imageUrl))
                                            {
                                                <img class="person-avatar" src="@imageUrl" alt="@originalName"
                                                     onerror="this.style.display='none';this.nextElementSibling.style.display='flex';" />
                                                <span class="person-avatar-placeholder" style="display:none;">
                                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="silhouette-icon"><circle cx="32" cy="24" r="12"/><ellipse cx="32" cy="56" rx="20" ry="14"/></svg>
                                                </span>
                                            }
                                            else
                                            {
                                                <span class="person-avatar-placeholder">
                                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="silhouette-icon"><circle cx="32" cy="24" r="12"/><ellipse cx="32" cy="56" rx="20" ry="14"/></svg>
                                                </span>
                                            }
                                            <span class="person-name">@originalName</span>
                                        </span>
                                    }
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        }

                        @if (detailReviews.Count > 0)
                        {
                            <div class="detail-section">
                                <h3>Critic Reviews</h3>
                                @foreach (var (review, score) in detailReviews)
                                {
                                    <div class="review-item">
                                        @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(score))
                                        {
                                            <span class="review-score">@score</span>
                                        }
                                        <span class="review-text">@review</span>
                                    </div>
                                }
                            </div>
                        }
                    </div>
                }
                else
                {
                <div class="panel">
                    <h3>Results (@resp.MediaResults.Count)</h3>
                    <div class="poster-grid">
                        @foreach (var json in resp.MediaResults)
                        {
                            var docType = GetProp(json, "type") ?? "movie";

                            @if (docType == "movie")
                            {
                                var displayTitle = GetProp(json, "originalTitle") ?? GetProp(json, "title") ?? "";
                                var year = GetProp(json, "year") ?? "";
                                var rating = GetProp(json, "mpaaRating") ?? "";
                                var poster = GetProp(json, "posterUrl");

                                <div class="poster-card">
                                    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(poster))
                                    {
                                        <img class="poster-img" src="@poster" alt="@displayTitle" loading="lazy" />
                                    }
                                    else
                                    {
                                        <div class="poster-img-placeholder">🎬</div>
                                    }
                                    <div class="poster-info">
                                        <div class="poster-title">@displayTitle</div>
                                        <div class="poster-meta-row">
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(year)) { <span class="poster-year">@year</span> }
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(rating)) { <span class="poster-rating">@rating</span> }
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            }
                            else if (docType == "person")
                            {
                                var movieTitle = GetProp(json, "movieTitle") ?? "";
                                var poster = GetProp(json, "posterUrl");
                                var releaseDate = GetProp(json, "releaseDate") ?? "";
                                var rating = GetProp(json, "mpaaRating") ?? "";
                                var roles = GetRoles(json);

                                @if (roles.Count > 0)
                                {
                                    @foreach (var role in roles)
                                    {
                                        <div class="poster-card">
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(role.PosterUrl))
                                            {
                                                <img class="poster-img" src="@role.PosterUrl" alt="@role.MovieTitle" loading="lazy" />
                                            }
                                            else
                                            {
                                                <div class="poster-img-placeholder">🎬</div>
                                            }
                                            <div class="poster-info">
                                                <div class="poster-title">@role.MovieTitle</div>
                                                <div class="poster-meta-row">
                                                    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(role.Year)) { <span class="poster-year">@role.Year</span> }
                                                    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(role.MpaaRating)) { <span class="poster-rating">@role.MpaaRating</span> }
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    }
                                }
                                else
                                {
                                    <div class="poster-card">
                                        @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(poster))
                                        {
                                            <img class="poster-img" src="@poster" alt="@movieTitle" loading="lazy" />
                                        }
                                        else
                                        {
                                            <div class="poster-img-placeholder">🎬</div>
                                        }
                                        <div class="poster-info">
                                            <div class="poster-title">@movieTitle</div>
                                            <div class="poster-meta-row">
                                                @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(releaseDate)) { <span class="poster-year">@releaseDate</span> }
                                                @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(rating)) { <span class="poster-rating">@rating</span> }
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    };
}

